channel.title: Compiling error please help
channel.description:
trying to make a kill command and this happened [code]client.java:11033: error: cannot find symbol c.appendHit(255, 0); ^ symbol: method appendHit(int,int) location: variable c of type client Note: ControlPanel.java uses unchecked or unsafe operations. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:unchecked for details. 1 error Finished! Press any key to continue . . .
[/code]

item.title: Compiling error please help
item.dc:creator: @blazeitup blazeitup
item.description:
@blazeitup wrote:

client.java:11033: error: cannot find symbol
c.appendHit(255, 0);
^
symbol: method appendHit(int,int)
location: variable c of type client

All it is is that ur missing a symbol which is “method appendhit(int,int)” All you need to do is add that symbol but sadly idk what one that is. just ho to google and search "rsps compiler error method appendHit(int,int) and you should get a answer.
